org.fhnw.aigs.server.common

Class LogRouter

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.fhnw.aigs.server.common.LogRouter

  • public class LogRouter
extends java.lang.Object
    Class to manage the server-side logging. It supersede standard logging for better control of the formats, outputs and levels of the logs.
    The class uses the Java SE standard logger in the backend.
    Possible log levels are Severe, Warning, System (messages of the AIGS server), Game (messages of AIGS games on the server) and Info.
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Raphael Stoeckli (26.02.2015)

      • setUpLogging

        public static void setUpLogging()
        This method is responsible for the logging by setting a FileHandler. Usually the log files will be saved to the folder "logs", under the name "aigs.log". Logs which exceed 10 MB in size will trigger the creation of a new logfile.

      • processMessage

        private static java.lang.String processMessage(java.lang.String input)
        Method to route the custom message. In case of XML style, XMLHelper.prettyPrintXml(java.lang.String) will be used. Otherwise the input will not be changed. In case of the style "discard" an empty string will be returned.
        Parameters:
        input - Message to process
        Returns:
        Processed message
